---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import { docsNavigation } from '../../data/docsNavigation';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Neuwerk Firewall Documentation"
  description="A stripped-down documentation scaffold organized around how the firewall is designed, deployed, and operated."
>
  <p>
    This docs scaffold is ready for product documentation, not contributor onboarding. The current
    hierarchy starts with the system model, then moves into configuration, deployment, operations,
    interfaces, and reference material.
  </p>

  <h2 id="recommended-structure">Recommended Structure</h2>
  <p>
    Start by filling in the architecture pages first. They establish the dataplane and control-plane
    split, the supported traffic flows, and the cluster model that the rest of the docs depend on.
  </p>

  <p>
    After that, document configuration and deployment together so operators can move from policy
    concepts into concrete rollout shapes. Operations should come next, followed by interface and
    reference pages once the main workflows are stable.
  </p>

  <div class="not-prose mt-10 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
    {docsNavigation.map((section) => (
      <section class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-5">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">{section.title}</h3>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-300">
          {section.items.map((item) => (
            <li>
              <a href={item.href} class="transition-colors hover:text-white">
                {item.label}
              </a>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </section>
    ))}
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
